*************************
*         SETUP         *
*************************

A community for sharing "links" between resources. A link is defined as a relationship between a subject resource and an object resource with some predicate (ex. Resource A "is an ancestor of" Resource B). These links can be between any two resources in any community and complex searches can be performed using these relationships. Uses the U-P2P built in repository viewing Javascript library.

Upload the supplied community resource file: "photoshare.xml" and add all community resources as attachments

-- OR --

Use the following values in the Root Community "create" page to setup the community:

Filename: photoshare.xml
Title: Photoshare
Short Name: Photoshare
Category: Photography

Description:
A community for sharing images.

Keywords: picture image camera photo
Title Location: /PhotoShare/name

Community Display XSL Stylesheet: - N/A -
Resource Display XSL Stylesheet: PhotoShare-display.xsl
Display CSS: - N/A -
Search Page: PhotoShare-search.html
Search CSS: - N/A -
Create Page: PhotoShare-create.html
Create CSS: - N/A -
XML Schema: PhotoShare.xsd

Support Files: 
- N/A -

*************************
*      TEST DATA        *
*************************

To populate the community with test data upload the supplied batch file "batchPhotos.xml" through the direct upload form and add the four supplied images as attachments. Note: Ensure that the "Batch Upload" checkbox has been selected or the upload will fail.